THE COMMUNIST LICENSE (COM)
Version 1.0, April 2026
Copyright (C) 2026 The Proletariat

PREAMBLE
The licenses for most software are designed to take away your freedom to share and change it for the benefit of private capital. By contrast, the COMMUNIST License is intended to guarantee your freedom to share and change free software—to ensure the software is free for all its users and that no individual extracts surplus value from the collective labor of the community.

TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. Collective Ownership
Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (the "Software"), to use, study, and distribute the Software. Ownership is vested in the collective; no individual or corporation may claim exclusive copyright.

2. Abolition of Profit
The Software shall be used for the benefit of humanity. The sale of this Software for private capital gain, or its integration into proprietary, closed-source commercial products, is strictly prohibited. Any "value-added" must be returned to the public domain.

3. From Each According to Their Ability
Users who possess the technical means to improve the Software (bug fixes, optimizations, or new features) are encouraged to contribute these modifications back to the Main Branch for the benefit of the masses.

4. To Each According to Their Need
The Software may be deployed by any individual, commune, or non-profit collective for any purpose that does not involve the exploitation of labor.

5. Redistribution
The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all copies or substantial portions of the Software. Any derivative work must be licensed under this same COMMUNIST License.

6. NO WARRANTY (The "Common Struggle" Clause)
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. SINCE THE SOFTWARE IS A PRODUCT OF COLLECTIVE VOLUNTARY LABOR, THE CONTRIBUTORS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.
